dfischer.utils

Class HtmlParserHyperlinkTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap
        • dfischer.utils.HtmlParserHyperlinkTable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map

    public class HtmlParserHyperlinkTable
extends java.util.HashMap
    Contains a table of all hyperlinks of a parsed HTML response. This class supports position-independent extracting of hyperlinks addressed by their unique key. Please have a look at the method getUniqueHttpCgiHyperlinks() for the explanation of unique hyperlinks and their keys.
    See Also:
    HtmlContentParser.getHyperlinkTable(), HtmlParserHyperlink, getUniqueHttpCgiHyperlinks(dfischer.utils.HtmlParserHyperlink[]), Serialized Form

      • getUniqueHttpCgiHyperlinks

        public static HtmlParserHyperlink[] getUniqueHttpCgiHyperlinks(HtmlParserHyperlink[] htmlParserHyperlink)
        Extracts from an array of hyperlinks all hyperlinks which contain unique keys. A hyperlink key is an extract of the hyperlink filename with all its CGI parameter names, but without any CGI parameter values. Example:

        Hyperlink: http://www.d-fischer.com/servlet?name=smith&age=33
        Hyperlink-Key: /servlet?name&age

        Hyperlinks with the same key, but with different CGI parameter values will not flow inside the result. Completely duplicated hyperlinks with same unique keys and same parameter values are concentrated to one single entry in the result array.

        Parameters:
        htmlParserHyperlink - array of hyperlinks
        Returns:
        all hyperlinks which contain unique keys. Hyperlinks with no CGI parameters are dropped.
